=Georgia=

<font size=3>Georgia was a region of the former Soviet Union and became an independent republic in 1991. Meter stamps with former Soviet Union markings (“CCCP”, hammer & sickle logo) are known, but stamps with Soviet inscriptions removed or with the new country name inscribed have not been reported. It is most likely that such stamps exist and we just do not know about them.</font>

